<includeonly>{{#ask: [[-Has subobject::{{{page|{{FULLPAGENAME}}}}}]] [[Category:{{{category|}}}]]
 | link=none
 | format=template
 | template={{{category|}}}/subobject-row
 | named args=yes
 | sort=Has sort order
 | order=asc
}}</includeonly><noinclude>
All subobjects of a single category on a page, dispatched through the
auto-generated `<category>/subobject-row` template so each row uses
the dispatcher's baked-params fast path. One `#ask` regardless of
subobject count.

Differs from Category/subobjects: takes one explicit subobject
category and skips the ancestor walk. Use when you want one specific
subobject type in a custom display; use Category/subobjects when you
want all subobject types auto-discovered from the inheritance chain.

Parameters: `category`, `page` (defaults to {{FULLPAGENAME}}).
</noinclude>
